-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Why non-commercial, and per-file exceptions
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
deepinme's data/ directory aggregates third-party psychometric items under
a mix of licenses (public domain, CC BY-NC-SA, research-only, etc.) — see
data/README.md and each file's `_meta` block for the authoritative,
file-level license. This repository's own CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 default is at
least as restrictive as every one of those source licenses, so it does not
conflict with any of them. Two things stay true regardless of this
repository's license, though:

  1. Items marked `license_class: "public_domain"` (the IPIP-derived sets)
     remain public domain on their own terms no matter how this repository
     is licensed — this repo's license governs deepinme's own compilation,
     translation, and original authorship, not the underlying public-domain
     text itself.
  2. This repository's non-commercial license applies to how THIRD PARTIES
     may use this public repository. It does not restrict the deepinme
     project's own contributors from later relicensing or commercializing
     their own original work (e.g. in a future paid product) — copyright
     in original contributions remains with their authors, who may always
     grant themselves different terms for their own material. It also does
     not, by itself, grant any additional rights over the non-public-domain
     third-party content beyond what each source's own license already
     allows (see data/reference/licensing.json).
